Dorothy Hyson https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dorothy_Hyson 0 Dorothy Hyson, Lady Quayle, was born Dorothy Wardell Heisen, (December 24, 1914 – May 23, 1996) in Chicago, USA. She was a successful American film and stage actress who worked largely in England. During World War II she worked as a cryptographer at Bletchley Park.
